<comment type="function">
<text evidence="3 4 5">Sugar-phosphate phosphohydrolase that appears to contribute to butanol tolerance (PubMed:27941785). Catalyzes the dephosphorylation of D-mannitol 1-phosphate and D-sorbitol 6-phosphate (PubMed:27941785). Is also able to dephosphorylate other sugar phosphates in vitro including ribose-5-phosphate (Rib5P), 2-deoxyribose-5-phosphate, fructose-1-phosphate (Fru1P), fructose-6-phosphate (Fru6P), and glucose-6-phosphate (Glu6P) (PubMed:16990279). Selectively hydrolyzes beta-D-glucose-1-phosphate (bGlu1P) and has no activity with the alpha form (PubMed:16990279).</text>
</comment>
<comment type="catalytic activity">
<reaction evidence="4">
<text>Sugar phosphate + H(2)O = sugar + phosphate.</text>
